<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4920] DIH JdbcDataSource exception handling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4920</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JdbcDataSource will incorrectly suppress exceptions when retrieving a connection from a JNDI context and fall back to trying to use DriverManager to obtain a connection. This makes it impossible to troubleshoot misconfigured JNDI DataSource.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Additionally, when a SQLException is thrown while initializing a connection, such as in setAutoCommit(), the connection will not be closed. This can cause a resource leak.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A patch will be attached with unit tests that addresses both issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
